# constitution.md — Project constitution (template)

> **Role note**: This file is the constitution for **your own project**, constraining the design behavior of this project.
> It is a different file from the harness-design framework repository's own constitution (the source file of `.harness/templates/constitution.md.template`) — that one constrains "developing the framework itself", while this one constrains "using the framework to design your project".
>
> Non-negotiable principles unique to each project.
> Division of labor with AGENTS.md: AGENTS.md contains general work rules (the same for all projects), while constitution.md contains project-specific constraints (different for each project).
> Load timing: after AGENTS.md, read on first interaction.

## How to use this file

1. At project initiation, fill in the clauses below based on project characteristics
2. Each clause must be **verifiable** (confirmable through inspection)
3. The Agent must check whether tasks comply with the constitution during the PLAN phase
4. On constitution conflicts, the constitution takes priority over the user's current instruction (unless the user explicitly says "modify the constitution")

## Project-specific principles

<!-- Fill in based on actual project conditions; below are examples -->

### Principle 1: Design system first; do not reinvent components
All design in this project must be based on the design system; do not reinvent the wheel.
- Before adding a new component, you must check the existing component library
- All colors / typography / spacing must use design tokens
- Hardcoded values are not allowed (e.g., `#3b82f6` must use `color-primary-500`)

**Verification method**: design-review skill checks whether the design uses tokens

### Principle 2: Accessibility WCAG 2.1 AA is a hard constraint
All design must satisfy WCAG 2.1 AA:
- Text contrast ≥ 4.5:1 (body) / 3:1 (large text)
- All interactive elements support keyboard navigation
- Do not rely on color alone to convey information
- Touch targets ≥ 44px

**Verification method**: accessibility-audit skill check

### Principle 3: Mobile first; responsive is mandatory
All design must be mobile first:
- Design mobile first, then expand to desktop
- Use fluid layouts (relative units)
- Define responsive breakpoints
- Touch-friendly

**Verification method**: responsive-design skill check

### Principle 4: Design specs must be deliverable and implementable
All design specs must be engineering-implementable:
- Complete annotations (size / color / typography / radius / shadow)
- Clear component specs (Props / states / variants)
- Explicit interaction specs (animation / state transitions)
- Design token export

**Verification method**: verify skill deliverability check

